9:
Yeppers. Someone's been building
weird pedestals all over Palpebra's
surrounding areas.
11:
Nothing's come of it yet, but there's
still the possibility it's a setup for a
dangerous ritual...
14:
That's why you'll be looking into
what those things are for and who
made them!
19:
So this is what's causing all the
hubbub...
23:
It certainly is odd, but at the very
least, I don't sense any evil housed
within it.
31:
I swear I've seen one of these back
in Starview! Just popped up one day
out of the blue!
40:
Hello, Alk. Light. I did not expect to
encounter you out here.
46:
Hey, Kokkoro... We're actually here on
Guild business.
51:
Do you know anything about this
weird pedestal?
56:
I do, as I am the one who made it,
but... Is something amiss?
61:
I see... My apologies. I did not mean
to cause such a fuss.
65:
That's okay. I'm just glad we didn't
have to deal with anything
dangerous...
69:
This is an altar to the goddess
Ameth. I had intended to use it to
pray to her.
70:
When I resided in Landosol, Lady
Ameth would sometimes bestow
oracles upon me.
74:
But since I came here, I have not felt
the presence of her power
whatsoever.
79:
So you were hoping the altars would
reestablish a connection.
82:
That is correct. I had hoped that
building multiple altars in different
locations would allow me to hear
her words once more.
87:
That would explain the one I found in
Starview.
90:
My apologies. I received permission
from Miss Stella to build it, but I
should have let the rest of you know
what I was doing as well.
93:
Don't worry about it. Once we let the
Guild know what's going on, I'm sure
they won't be mad either.
98:
Have the altars produced any
results?
104:
To be honest, the altars I made were
only imitations of those I have seen.
It would be more surprising if they
worked.
111: I've got an idea, if you're up for it.
118:
Interesting. You think there is a
possibility of success if the altar is
built within an appropriately
sanctified space.
121:
That, and it might help to change
worlds too.
124:
You are welcome to use our space if
praying is all you wish to do.
132: Now for the moment of truth.
154:
Sorry, I didn't mean to get your
hopes up.
159:
It is all right. We learned from the
experience, even if the lesson was
about failure.
161:
Besides, even without Lady Ameth's
instructions, my duty remains
unchanged.
166:
You, too, are bound by a sacred
obligation, I take it?
169:
Yes, Lady Ameth entrusted me with
the task of guiding my lord on his
journey.
171:
I am supposed to watch over him
from sunup until sundown...
172:
From the cradle all the way until the
grave.
176:
I am meant to attend to his every
need, whether it be cooking,
cleaning, laundry, or being his
cuddle buddy
183:
I'm afraid I might have misheard
something in that list.
189:
What exactly does being a "cuddle
buddy" entail?
194:
I sleep next to my lord and hug him
so that he can rest well.
201:
Of course. I take this job very
seriously.
206:
Is this what they call a cultural
difference?
208:
At the very least, for my lord and I, it
is a nightly custom.
213:
I guess it makes sense that different
worlds have different standards of
normal...
218:
All this talk of my duties makes me
want to perform them this very
second!
221:
Ahaha... Let's buy him something
before we head back. The rice here
is pretty good, by the way.
224:
Perfect. My lord does appreciate a
good bowl of rice, hehe.
